{"title_page": "Sofia Helin", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name            = Sofia Helin\n| image           = Sofia Helin 2012 (cropped).jpg\n| imagesize       = \n| alt             = \n| caption         = Helin in 2012\n| birth_name      = Sofia Margareta Helin\n| birth_date      = {{Birth date and age|1972|4|25|df=y}}\n| birth_place     = [[Hovsta]], [[Sweden]]\n| othername       = \n| occupation      = Actress\n| spouse          = Daniel G\u00f6tschenhjelm\n| domesticpartner = \n| website         = \n}}\n'''Sofia Margareta G\u00f6tschenhjelm Helin''' (born 25 April 1972) is a [[Sweden|Swedish]] actress. She was nominated for a [[Guldbagge Award]] for her role in ''[[Dalecarlians (film)|Dalecarlians]]'', and stars as [[Saga Nor\u00e9n]] in the Danish/Swedish co-produced TV series ''[[The Bridge (Danish/Swedish TV series)|The Bridge]]'' (Danish: Broen; Swedish: Bron).\n\n==Early life and education==\nSofia Helin was born in [[Hovsta]] in [[\u00d6rebro]], [[N\u00e4rke]]. Her father was a salesman and her mother was a nurse.<ref name=TheTimes>{{cite news |url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/arts/tv-radio/article3992299.ece |title=Sofia Helin&nbsp;\u2013 the star who turned Saturday night into Scandi-night |last1=Thomson |first1=Alice |last2=Sylvester |first2=Rachel |date=1 February 2014 |newspaper=[[The Times]] |access-date=4 February 2014 |url-access=subscription }}</ref>  When she was 10 days old, her grandmother and her six-year-old brother were in a car accident; her grandmother survived, but her brother was killed.<ref name=TheGuardian>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2016/jan/01/sofia-helin-my-family-values |title=Sofia Helin: My Family Values |last=Lewis |first=Roz |date=1 January 2016 |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |access-date=2 January 2016}}</ref> From 1994-1996, she went to Calle Flygares theatre school and graduated from the [[Stockholm Theatre Academy]] in 2001. She was brought up in [[Linghem, Sweden|Linghem]], outside [[Link\u00f6ping]] but in 2015 was living in [[Stockholm]].<ref name=SAS>{{cite web |last1=Agorelius |first1=Monika |title=Meet Sofia Helin \u2013 star of crime series 'The Bridge' |url=https://scandinaviantraveler.com/en/people/meet-sofia-helin-star-of-crime-series-the-bridge |accessdate=13 December 2015 |publisher=[[SAS Group|SAS]] |website=Scandinavian Traveller |date=30 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nHer films include ''[[At Point Blank]]'' (''R\u00e5narna'') (2003) playing the leading role of Chief Inspector Klara. In 2004, she took the leading role of Mia in ''[[Masj\u00e4vlar]]'', and she was nominated for a Guldbagge award.<ref name=TheTelegraph/> Followed by, in 2007, the leading role of Cecilia Algottsdotter in ''[[Arn (film)|Arn]]'', an adaptation of [[Jan Guillou]]'s ''[[The Knight Templar (Crusades trilogy)|The Knight Templar]]'', about [[Arn Magnusson]]. She also featured in the Swedish animated film ''[[Metropia (film)|Metropia]]'' (2009).\n\nSince 2012, she has become famous outside Sweden as a result of the successful crime drama series, ''[[The Bridge (Danish/Swedish TV series)|The Bridge]]'', in which she played Saga Nor\u00e9n, the homicide detective from [[Malm\u00f6]].<ref name=\"love/hate\">{{cite magazine |last1=Dowell |first1=Ben |title=The Bridge's Sofia Helin: my love/hate relationship with Saga Noren |url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2015-11-21/the-bridges-sofia-helin-my-lovehate-relationship-with-saga-noren |accessdate=7 December 2015 |magazine=Radio Times |date=21 November 2015}}</ref> In the UK, the series attracted more than a million viewers per episode and she has been called a role model for women with [[Asperger syndrome]]. She said she would appear in a fourth series.<ref name=BBCRole>{{cite web |last1=Townsend |first1=Lucy |title=How The Bridge's heroine became a role model for women with Autism |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/disability-34995327 |accessdate=9 December 2015 |website=BBC News |date=9 December 2015}}</ref><ref name=TheTelegraph>{{cite news |last1=Williams |first1=Sally |title=The Bridge's Sofia Helin: 'Playing Saga is like a vice gripping my body' |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/12012627/The-Bridges-Sofia-Helin-Playing-Saga-is-like-a-vice-gripping-my-body.html |accessdate=29 November 2015 |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |date=28 November 2015}}</ref> The fourth season began airing in Sweden and Denmark on 1 January 2018 and in May 2018 in the UK.\n\nIn 2015, she starred in a Danish science fiction film called ''Fang Rung''<ref name=FangRung>{{cite magazine |last1=Barraclough |first1=Leo |title=Global Screen Acquires Sci-fi Thriller \u2018Fang Rung\u2019 Starring \u2018The Bridge\u2019 Actress Sofia Helin |url=https://variety.com/2015/film/global/global-screen-acquires-sci-fi-thriller-fang-rung-starring-the-bridge-actress-sofia-helin-1201509201/ |accessdate=14 December 2015 |magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=1 June 2015}}</ref> and acted in a British/German TV series directed by [[Oliver Hirschbiegel]], shot in Prague, about divided Berlin in the 1970s and called ''[[The_Same_Sky_(TV_series)|The Same Sky]]'' in which she spoke in both German and English.<ref name=Nordisk>{{cite web |last1=Pham |first1=Annika |title=Sofia Helin: \"A role has to turn me on\" |url=http://www.nordiskfilmogtvfond.com/index.php/news/stories/sofia-helin-role-has-turn-me/ |accessdate=14 December 2015 |website=Nordisk Film & TV Fond |date=25 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHelin is married to Daniel G\u00f6tschenhjelm, a priest in the [[Church of Sweden]] and former actor whom she met at drama school.<ref name=TheTelegraph/> She has two children: a son, Ossian, aged {{Age|2003|8|12|df=y}} and a daughter, Nike, aged {{Years ago|2009}}.<ref name=RadioTimes/> Helin is a Christian.<ref name=SAS/>\n\nHelin\u2019s facial scar was caused by a cycling accident when she was 24.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2012/may/12/bridge-sofia-helin-saga-interview |title=Move over, Sarah Lund: The Bridge star Sofia Helin interviewed |last=Khaleeli |first=Homa |date=12 May 2012 |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=11 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/features/the-view-from-the-bridge-sofia-helin-on-weird-sex-and-playing-tvs-most-awkward-copper-9016735.html |title=The view from The Bridge: Sofia Helin on weird sex and playing TV's most awkward copper |last=Mesure |first=Susie |date=29 December 2013 |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |access-date=25 January 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n*''[[Rederiet]]'' (1997)\n*''[[Tusenbr\u00f6der]]'' (2002)\n*''[[Beck \u2013 Sista vittnet]]'' (2002)\n*''[[At Point Blank]]'' (2003)\n*''[[Four Shades of Brown]]'' (2004)\n*''[[Dalecarlians (film)|Dalecarlians]]'' (''Masj\u00e4vlar'') (2004)\n*''[[Blodsbr\u00f6der]]'' (2005)\n*''[[Nina Frisk]]'' (2007)\n*''[[Arn \u2013 The Knight Templar]]'' (2007)\n*''[[Arn \u2013 The Kingdom at Road's End]]'' (2008)\n*''[[Metropia (film)|Metropia]]'' - Swedish animated film (2009)\n*''[[G\u00e5ten Ragnarok]]'' (2013)\n*''[[The Bridge (Danish/Swedish TV series)|The Bridge]]'' (''Broen/Bron'') - TV series<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1733785/ |title=The Bridge (2011\u2013) |website=IMDb |access-date=7 December 2015}}</ref> (2011\u20132018)\n*''[[The Same Sky (TV series)|The Same Sky]]'' - TV series (2017)\n*''[[That Good Night (film)|That Good Night]]'' (2017)\n*''[[The Snowman (2017 film)|The Snowman]]'' (2017)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*{{IMDb name|0375138}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Helin, Sofia}}\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from \u00d6rebro Municipality]]\n[[Category:People from N\u00e4rke]]\n[[Category:Swedish film actresses]]\n[[Category:Swedish television actresses]]\n[[Category:20th-century Swedish actresses]]\n[[Category:Swedish Christians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Swedish actresses]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name            = Sofia Helin\n| image           = Sofia Helin 2012 (cropped).jpg\n| imagesize       = \n| alt             = \n| caption         = Helin in 2012\n| birth_name      = Sofia Margareta Helin\n| birth_date      = {{Birth date and age|1972|4|25|df=y}}\n| birth_place     = [[Hovsta]], [[Sweden]]\n| othername       = \n| occupation      = Actress\n| spouse          = Daniel G\u00f6tschenhjelm\n| domesticpartner = \n| website         = \n}}\n'''Sofia Margareta G\u00f6tschenhjelm Helin''' (born 25 April 1972) is a [[Sweden|Swedish]] actress. She was nominated for a [[Guldbagge Award]] for her role in ''[[Dalecarlians (film)|Dalecarlians]]'', and stars as [[Saga Nor\u00e9n]] in the Danish/Swedish co-produced TV series ''[[The Bridge (Danish/Swedish TV series)|The Bridge]]'' (Danish: Broen; Swedish: Bron).\n\n==Early life and education==\nSofia Helin was born in [[Hovsta]] in [[\u00d6rebro]], [[N\u00e4rke]]. Her father was a salesman and her mother was a nurse.<ref name=TheTimes>{{cite news |url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/arts/tv-radio/article3992299.ece |title=Sofia Helin&nbsp;\u2013 the star who turned Saturday night into Scandi-night |last1=Thomson |first1=Alice |last2=Sylvester |first2=Rachel |date=1 February 2014 |newspaper=[[The Times]] |access-date=4 February 2014 |url-access=subscription }}</ref>  When she was 10 days old, her grandmother and her six-year-old brother were in a car accident; her grandmother survived, but her brother was killed.<ref name=TheGuardian>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2016/jan/01/sofia-helin-my-family-values |title=Sofia Helin: My Family Values |last=Lewis |first=Roz |date=1 January 2016 |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |access-date=2 January 2016}}</ref> From 1994-1996, she went to Calle Flygares theatre school and graduated from the [[Stockholm Theatre Academy]] in 2001. She was brought up in [[Linghem, Sweden|Linghem]], outside [[Link\u00f6ping]] but in 2015 was living in [[Stockholm]].<ref name=SAS>{{cite web |last1=Agorelius |first1=Monika |title=Meet Sofia Helin \u2013 star of crime series 'The Bridge' |url=https://scandinaviantraveler.com/en/people/meet-sofia-helin-star-of-crime-series-the-bridge |accessdate=13 December 2015 |publisher=[[SAS Group|SAS]] |website=Scandinavian Traveller |date=30 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nHer films include ''[[At Point Blank]]'' (''R\u00e5narna'') (2003) playing the leading role of Chief Inspector Klara. In 2004, she took the leading role of Mia in ''[[Masj\u00e4vlar]]'', and she was nominated for a Guldbagge award.<ref name=TheTelegraph/> Followed by, in 2007, the leading role of Cecilia Algottsdotter in ''[[Arn (film)|Arn]]'', an adaptation of [[Jan Guillou]]'s ''[[The Knight Templar (Crusades trilogy)|The Knight Templar]]'', about [[Arn Magnusson]]. She also featured in the Swedish animated film ''[[Metropia (film)|Metropia]]'' (2009).\n\nSince 2012, she has become famous outside Sweden as a result of the successful crime drama series, ''[[The Bridge (Danish/Swedish TV series)|The Bridge]]'', in which she played Saga Nor\u00e9n, the homicide detective from [[Malm\u00f6]].<ref name=\"love/hate\">{{cite magazine |last1=Dowell |first1=Ben |title=The Bridge's Sofia Helin: my love/hate relationship with Saga Noren |url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2015-11-21/the-bridges-sofia-helin-my-lovehate-relationship-with-saga-noren |accessdate=7 December 2015 |magazine=Radio Times |date=21 November 2015}}</ref> In the UK, the series attracted more than a million viewers per episode and she has been called a role model for women with [[Asperger syndrome]]. She said she would appear in a fourth series.<ref name=BBCRole>{{cite web |last1=Townsend |first1=Lucy |title=How The Bridge's heroine became a role model for women with Autism |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/disability-34995327 |accessdate=9 December 2015 |website=BBC News |date=9 December 2015}}</ref><ref name=TheTelegraph>{{cite news |last1=Williams |first1=Sally |title=The Bridge's Sofia Helin: 'Playing Saga is like a vice gripping my body' |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/12012627/The-Bridges-Sofia-Helin-Playing-Saga-is-like-a-vice-gripping-my-body.html |accessdate=29 November 2015 |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |date=28 November 2015}}</ref> The fourth season began airing in Sweden and Denmark on 1 January 2018 and in May 2018 in the UK.\n\nIn 2015, she starred in a Danish science fiction film called ''Fang Rung''<ref name=FangRung>{{cite magazine |last1=Barraclough |first1=Leo |title=Global Screen Acquires Sci-fi Thriller \u2018Fang Rung\u2019 Starring \u2018The Bridge\u2019 Actress Sofia Helin |url=https://variety.com/2015/film/global/global-screen-acquires-sci-fi-thriller-fang-rung-starring-the-bridge-actress-sofia-helin-1201509201/ |accessdate=14 December 2015 |magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=1 June 2015}}</ref> and acted in a British/German TV series directed by [[Oliver Hirschbiegel]], shot in Prague, about divided Berlin in the 1970s and called ''[[The_Same_Sky_(TV_series)|The Same Sky]]'' in which she spoke in both German and English.<ref name=Nordisk>{{cite web |last1=Pham |first1=Annika |title=Sofia Helin: \"A role has to turn me on\" |url=http://www.nordiskfilmogtvfond.com/index.php/news/stories/sofia-helin-role-has-turn-me/ |accessdate=14 December 2015 |website=Nordisk Film & TV Fond |date=25 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHelin is married to Daniel G\u00f6tschenhjelm, a priest in the [[Church of Sweden]] and former actor whom she met at drama school.<ref name=TheTelegraph/> She has two children: a son, Ossian, aged {{Years ago|2003}} and a daughter, Nike, aged {{Years ago|2009}}.<ref name=RadioTimes/> Helin is a Christian.<ref name=SAS/>\n\nHelin\u2019s facial scar was caused by a cycling accident when she was 24.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2012/may/12/bridge-sofia-helin-saga-interview |title=Move over, Sarah Lund: The Bridge star Sofia Helin interviewed |last=Khaleeli |first=Homa |date=12 May 2012 |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=11 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/features/the-view-from-the-bridge-sofia-helin-on-weird-sex-and-playing-tvs-most-awkward-copper-9016735.html |title=The view from The Bridge: Sofia Helin on weird sex and playing TV's most awkward copper |last=Mesure |first=Susie |date=29 December 2013 |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |access-date=25 January 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n*''[[Rederiet]]'' (1997)\n*''[[Tusenbr\u00f6der]]'' (2002)\n*''[[Beck \u2013 Sista vittnet]]'' (2002)\n*''[[At Point Blank]]'' (2003)\n*''[[Four Shades of Brown]]'' (2004)\n*''[[Dalecarlians (film)|Dalecarlians]]'' (''Masj\u00e4vlar'') (2004)\n*''[[Blodsbr\u00f6der]]'' (2005)\n*''[[Nina Frisk]]'' (2007)\n*''[[Arn \u2013 The Knight Templar]]'' (2007)\n*''[[Arn \u2013 The Kingdom at Road's End]]'' (2008)\n*''[[Metropia (film)|Metropia]]'' - Swedish animated film (2009)\n*''[[G\u00e5ten Ragnarok]]'' (2013)\n*''[[The Bridge (Danish/Swedish TV series)|The Bridge]]'' (''Broen/Bron'') - TV series<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1733785/ |title=The Bridge (2011\u2013) |website=IMDb |access-date=7 December 2015}}</ref> (2011\u20132018)\n*''[[The Same Sky (TV series)|The Same Sky]]'' - TV series (2017)\n*''[[That Good Night (film)|That Good Night]]'' (2017)\n*''[[The Snowman (2017 film)|The Snowman]]'' (2017)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*{{IMDb name|0375138}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Helin, Sofia}}\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from \u00d6rebro Municipality]]\n[[Category:People from N\u00e4rke]]\n[[Category:Swedish film actresses]]\n[[Category:Swedish television actresses]]\n[[Category:20th-century Swedish actresses]]\n[[Category:Swedish Christians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Swedish actresses]]\n", "name_user": "Catwolds", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sofia_Helin"}
